WEBVTT

00:01.367 --> 00:03.990
EDGAR: <i>The freezer
takes you to the Realm.</i>

00:03.990 --> 00:07.725
It's the only way everyone
will survive what's coming.

00:07.760 --> 00:10.027
I'm not going in, Holden
Matthews. You are.

00:10.029 --> 00:11.762
Our job is to protect that investment

00:11.798 --> 00:13.564
<i>as well as the belief system
of our clientele.</i>

00:13.600 --> 00:14.799
[GASPS]

00:14.834 --> 00:16.734
- We're under attack!
- [GUNSHOT]

00:16.769 --> 00:18.603
What's going on down there?

00:18.638 --> 00:19.904
Do you remember what I said about

00:19.939 --> 00:21.606
how you couldn't protect your son.

00:21.641 --> 00:22.840
I have a meeting with the FBI today.

00:22.876 --> 00:25.910
<i>If you ever cared about
me or Luke or Holden,</i>

00:25.945 --> 00:27.578
<i>come with me. It's your choice.</i>

00:27.614 --> 00:28.746
- [TIRES SQUEALING]
- [METALLIC CRUNCHING]

00:28.781 --> 00:30.514
LUKE: <i> I spoke to the FBI.</i>

00:30.550 --> 00:31.883
<i>They already have an investigation</i>

00:31.918 --> 00:32.917
going on for Hollow Sky.

00:32.952 --> 00:35.519
I really think that they can help us.

00:37.378 --> 00:38.444
[SPRAY HISSING]

00:38.479 --> 00:40.112
[SQUEAKING]

00:47.421 --> 00:48.387
LUKE: Look,

00:49.423 --> 00:51.123
I was the one that called Agent Borden.

00:52.226 --> 00:54.059
And-And this is my family.

00:54.095 --> 00:55.461
You and your grandfather

00:55.496 --> 00:57.262
don't need to implicate yourselves.

00:57.298 --> 00:58.397
We're already involved...

01:00.134 --> 01:01.300
[SIGHS] more than you know.

01:07.375 --> 01:10.209
Everything... Charlie said was true.

01:12.113 --> 01:14.246
All the time I was with Holden...

01:14.281 --> 01:17.015
I never wanted to think about
what it must be like for you...

01:18.319 --> 01:19.284
or your family.

01:20.521 --> 01:22.020
I was selfish.

01:23.324 --> 01:24.323
So...

01:26.427 --> 01:29.027
you could've helped him wake up.

01:31.532 --> 01:33.065
It's not that simple.

01:36.504 --> 01:38.404
I thought what we were doing was right.

01:41.342 --> 01:42.574
The only right thing to do

01:42.610 --> 01:45.444
is to ensure that no other
families have to suffer.

01:45.479 --> 01:46.478
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:47.515 --> 01:50.215
Agent Borden's just finishing up a call.

01:50.251 --> 01:51.517
Shouldn't be much longer.

01:51.552 --> 01:52.584
Thanks.

01:55.156 --> 01:56.188
WILLA: It'll be over soon.

01:57.525 --> 01:58.524
All of this.

01:59.560 --> 02:01.527
- Things can go back to being...
- Normal?

02:03.000 --> 02:09.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:10.104 --> 02:13.138
I know you said you wanted us
to stop seeing each other,

02:13.174 --> 02:15.207
and maybe you still feel
that way after today, but...

02:16.477 --> 02:18.510
right now, I'm really glad
you're by my side.

02:21.215 --> 02:22.247
Luke?

02:23.484 --> 02:24.450
Luke, what is it?

02:26.187 --> 02:27.219
WILLA: Luke?

02:28.556 --> 02:30.189
Sorry to keep you waiting.

02:31.392 --> 02:32.524
I'm Agent Gale Borden.

02:38.566 --> 02:40.466
Keep all the doors locked.
Don't let anyone in,

02:40.501 --> 02:42.534
especially if they say they're FBI.

02:42.570 --> 02:44.436
Willa, what is going on?

02:44.472 --> 02:46.205
Agent Borden isn't Agent Borden.

02:46.240 --> 02:48.140
<i>She's been asking about Hollow Sky</i>

02:48.175 --> 02:49.241
and about Arthur.

02:49.276 --> 02:50.342
We can't let her find that machine.

02:50.377 --> 02:53.512
- Willa, come home.
- WILLA: <i> Not yet.</i>

02:53.547 --> 02:56.448
Fake Borden knows about
the one at Hollow Sky.

02:56.484 --> 02:58.283
We have to get to it before she does.

02:58.319 --> 02:59.351
Until we know who she is

02:59.386 --> 03:00.519
<i>and what she wants with the technology.</i>

03:00.554 --> 03:02.054
Be careful, Willa.

03:03.357 --> 03:05.224
She could be dangerous.

03:05.259 --> 03:06.325
WILLA: <i> You too.</i>

03:09.263 --> 03:10.496
Dangerous?

03:10.531 --> 03:12.331
She knows you're not FBI.

03:13.534 --> 03:15.467
And she knows Hollow
Sky is your next stop.

03:15.503 --> 03:17.469
They're headed there now.

03:17.505 --> 03:19.271
Then I'd hate to keep them waiting.

03:20.441 --> 03:23.075
Everything in that lab
goes on the truck.

03:23.110 --> 03:24.076
Him too.

03:25.112 --> 03:26.111
DANIEL: Wait.

03:26.146 --> 03:27.346
You said you wouldn't hurt them.

03:27.381 --> 03:28.347
We had a deal.

03:29.416 --> 03:31.183
Arthur and Willa will be fine,

03:31.218 --> 03:32.317
so long as they co-operate.

03:34.121 --> 03:35.387
You did the right thing calling us.

03:35.422 --> 03:36.455
And just in the nick of time.

03:39.260 --> 03:40.292
Daniel,

03:40.327 --> 03:42.127
you know what's at stake.

03:43.264 --> 03:44.296
That technology...

03:45.499 --> 03:47.399
Arthur's life's work,

03:47.434 --> 03:50.302
is too valuable to abandon.

03:50.337 --> 03:51.436
Our cause...

03:52.473 --> 03:53.438
is too valuable.

03:55.209 --> 03:57.075
You'll see.

03:57.111 --> 03:59.211
History will vindicate our actions.

04:00.481 --> 04:02.180
What about my payment?

04:03.450 --> 04:05.083
You said I would be compensated.

04:08.155 --> 04:09.454
You're absolutely right.

04:11.225 --> 04:13.134
Pay the man what he's owed.

04:13.260 --> 04:14.293
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

04:15.396 --> 04:16.461
[GASPING]

04:21.334 --> 04:23.201
[DANIEL GROANING]

04:23.237 --> 04:25.037
I wanna be mobile within the hour.

04:31.045 --> 04:33.478
[RATTLING]

04:39.019 --> 04:42.187
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

04:44.491 --> 04:48.293
How was I supposed to know
the guy didn't have the key!

04:48.329 --> 04:50.128
EDGAR: I have a key.

04:50.164 --> 04:52.364
I hid it in a hollowed-out tree trunk,

04:52.399 --> 04:55.067
so no one would ever find it.

04:55.102 --> 04:58.170
This could all be going much
faster if I had some help.

05:02.142 --> 05:03.208
Hey, don't look at me.

05:03.243 --> 05:05.243
I'm not about to stick my
hand in some random tree.

05:06.981 --> 05:08.981
Do you have any idea what's
crawling around inside?

05:09.016 --> 05:11.249
You were in Afghanistan
with people shooting at you.

05:11.285 --> 05:13.285
Listen, arachnids have eight legs.

05:13.320 --> 05:15.354
I've never seen a Taliban insurgent

05:15.389 --> 05:16.388
with eight legs.

05:16.423 --> 05:18.256
EDGAR: I found it!

05:18.292 --> 05:20.258
[PANTING] I found it.

05:21.395 --> 05:23.095
[CHAIN RATTLING]

05:42.249 --> 05:44.282
Is everybody else seeing an empty box?

05:44.318 --> 05:46.985
[CHUCKLES] Is the universe empty?

05:47.021 --> 05:49.021
It's lined with Vantablack.

05:51.225 --> 05:53.992
A uniquely oriented microstructure

05:54.028 --> 05:55.027
of carbon nanotubes

05:55.062 --> 05:57.062
creating a substance so dark,

05:57.097 --> 05:59.331
it absorbs even the most powerful light.

06:02.970 --> 06:05.270
HOLDEN: You made a
sensory-deprivation tank...

06:05.305 --> 06:07.039
out of a freezer.

06:08.308 --> 06:10.208
Dr. Frost's and Dr. Foreman's machines,

06:10.244 --> 06:12.911
they'll transport your
consciousness, no problem.

06:12.946 --> 06:14.346
But not with this level of precision.

06:14.381 --> 06:16.948
Think of this as an express train

06:16.984 --> 06:18.283
to the heart of the Realm.

06:18.318 --> 06:19.384
Great. W-Well, let's go.

06:19.420 --> 06:21.219
Oh, wait. Not here.

06:21.255 --> 06:23.188
Wha... I thought you said it
was like the express train.

06:23.223 --> 06:26.058
Yes, but there are specific
points of intersection

06:26.093 --> 06:28.024
between our world and the Realm.

06:28.162 --> 06:29.261
Coordinates where the walls

06:29.296 --> 06:32.197
between worlds are more... malleable.

06:32.232 --> 06:34.032
My old house for example,

06:34.068 --> 06:36.134
um, where you crashed your
bike, the Bermuda Triangle.

06:36.170 --> 06:38.103
The Bermuda Triangle?

06:38.138 --> 06:40.439
How else do you explain all those
disaeapprig ships and planes?

06:40.474 --> 06:43.008
What do you think they disappeared to?

06:44.411 --> 06:47.212
My old house should provide
us with enough juice

06:47.247 --> 06:48.380
to power your journey.

06:50.217 --> 06:51.483
I just... hope it's still standing.

06:53.187 --> 06:54.186
Yeah, it's still standing.

06:55.255 --> 06:57.089
It's also tastefully remodeled

06:57.124 --> 06:59.257
and occupied by a family of four.

06:59.293 --> 07:00.392
So, what's the problem?

07:01.995 --> 07:06.098
Problem is we can't just ask
a family of strangers

07:06.133 --> 07:07.232
if we can use their house

07:07.267 --> 07:09.968
while I lock myself in
a 50-year-old freezer.

07:12.072 --> 07:13.371
So we get them out of the house.

07:16.009 --> 07:17.976
TESS: <i>On behalf of Dr.
Frost, I apologize</i>

07:18.011 --> 07:19.010
for your discomfort.

07:19.046 --> 07:21.012
I know it's not the ideal situation,

07:21.048 --> 07:23.248
but it is for your protection.

07:23.283 --> 07:25.984
MAN: Hey, what's going on?
Why are we here?

07:26.019 --> 07:28.019
We're running a systems test.

07:28.055 --> 07:30.055
And it's best to insulate you from any

07:30.090 --> 07:33.091
unforeseen gamma ray exposure.

07:33.127 --> 07:34.392
[CROWD MURMURING]

07:34.428 --> 07:37.028
In the mean time, we're
passing out waters

07:38.432 --> 07:40.298
and a snack and if you need
please ask one of us.

07:40.334 --> 07:41.967
We'll be happy to escort you.

07:42.002 --> 07:44.035
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

07:48.075 --> 07:49.307
[BABY WHIMPERING]

07:49.343 --> 07:52.244
Does this sort of thing happen often?

07:52.279 --> 07:54.146
No.

07:54.181 --> 07:56.214
But a systems test?

07:56.250 --> 07:58.250
It means we must be getting very close.

07:59.286 --> 08:00.285
Hmm.

08:04.124 --> 08:05.257
[DOOR SLAMS]

08:06.994 --> 08:08.059
What is it?

08:08.095 --> 08:10.028
I didn't get my snack.

08:10.063 --> 08:11.163
Now's really not the time.

08:11.198 --> 08:13.098
Time is running out.

08:13.133 --> 08:14.366
Those people are asking questions.

08:14.401 --> 08:16.935
How long until they start
asking about their friends?

08:16.970 --> 08:18.270
Their friends woke up.

08:18.305 --> 08:19.971
They're gone. They left.

08:20.007 --> 08:21.973
They're not our problem anymore.

08:22.009 --> 08:23.975
I've got five and a half
bodies that beg to differ.

08:25.078 --> 08:27.112
Guys you hired to protect your flock.

08:29.116 --> 08:30.248
Let's just cut 'em loose.

08:30.284 --> 08:31.383
Give these people back their money.

08:31.418 --> 08:32.984
Close our doors.

08:33.020 --> 08:35.253
Couple of months, and maybe
we can get that machine working.

08:35.289 --> 08:37.355
I don't have a couple of months.

08:38.424 --> 08:40.325
You were gonna leave.

08:40.360 --> 08:41.960
Still gonna.

08:41.995 --> 08:43.160
Our investors will hear about this

08:43.197 --> 08:45.063
and when they do, they'll
pull our funding.

08:45.098 --> 08:46.097
They'll confiscate everything.

08:46.133 --> 08:48.333
Technology, IP.

08:48.368 --> 08:49.367
What about Frost?

08:53.340 --> 08:55.006
I'm sure they'll take him too.

09:21.099 --> 09:24.200
This guy, the one you're looking
for, he threatened my son.

09:24.235 --> 09:25.368
He looked me right in the eyes and said

09:25.403 --> 09:26.782
he was going after Holden.

09:28.072 --> 09:30.072
We're all on edge, Tom.

09:30.108 --> 09:31.207
You gotta let me out of here.

09:31.242 --> 09:32.308
You gotta let me go.

09:33.411 --> 09:35.077
You know, you hear...

09:36.147 --> 09:39.982
about things like this
happening in other counties...

09:40.018 --> 09:42.385
the killing sprees and
multiple homicides...

09:42.420 --> 09:45.321
and you just... you think they
gotta be doing something wrong.

09:45.356 --> 09:47.189
TOM: Sheriff.

09:47.225 --> 09:49.158
Sheriff!

09:49.193 --> 09:51.427
Please, unlock this door and
let me go be with my family.

09:51.462 --> 09:53.396
I need to make sure that they're safe.

09:53.431 --> 09:54.430
Please!

09:56.301 --> 09:57.266
[DOORBELL RINGING]

09:59.404 --> 10:01.170
Hi there. Sorry to bother you.

10:01.205 --> 10:03.139
We're from the gas company.

10:03.174 --> 10:05.041
We're investigating a
busted main in the area,

10:05.076 --> 10:06.342
and they've got us
checking all nearby houses

10:06.377 --> 10:08.244
for possible contamination.

10:08.279 --> 10:09.412
Oh, my God.

10:09.447 --> 10:12.148
If we could just take a quick
look at your gas meter.

10:12.183 --> 10:13.282
Yes. Of course.

10:13.318 --> 10:15.151
- Come in.
- Right. Thank you.

10:16.421 --> 10:18.087
WOMAN: I think it's downstairs.

10:18.122 --> 10:19.255
CHARLIE: Perfect, lead the way.

10:27.432 --> 10:29.098
CHARLIE: Uh-oh.

10:29.133 --> 10:31.133
- What do you mean, "uh-oh"?
- [SIGHS]

10:31.169 --> 10:34.470
I'm picking up small traces
of carbon monoxide.

10:34.505 --> 10:37.206
I'm afraid we'll need you and
your family to vacate the house

10:37.241 --> 10:39.141
while we turn off the
gas and get this fixed.

10:43.381 --> 10:45.047
Where's your partner?

10:54.192 --> 10:56.092
- GIRL: Who are you?
- I'm Edgar.

10:57.362 --> 10:58.327
This used to be my room.

11:00.231 --> 11:01.997
And I haven't been here
in a very long time.

11:03.301 --> 11:04.433
Where did you go?

11:07.472 --> 11:08.437
Well...

11:16.047 --> 11:19.281
let's say this... is you...

11:20.418 --> 11:22.251
and... and this...

11:23.287 --> 11:24.420
is your consciousness.

11:29.160 --> 11:32.061
[MIMICKING WHOOSHING]

11:34.365 --> 11:35.998
[LAUGHS]

11:44.509 --> 11:46.242
Okay.

11:54.385 --> 11:56.085
[GUN CLICKS]

11:58.289 --> 12:00.055
Whoa, wh-wh-what are you doing?

12:00.091 --> 12:01.223
Just making sure we have enough bullets.

12:01.259 --> 12:02.258
Hey, wait, wait, wait, wait.

12:03.327 --> 12:04.994
This isn't your fault.

12:06.197 --> 12:08.197
Y-You don't have to do this.

12:09.400 --> 12:10.366
This isn't for me.

12:12.103 --> 12:14.203
The technology fell into
the wrong hands with Frost...

12:15.239 --> 12:17.973
and it almost cost Holden his life.

12:18.009 --> 12:20.376
I'm sure there were others
who weren't so lucky.

12:20.411 --> 12:23.212
This isn't going to end
until that machine is destroyed.

12:28.119 --> 12:29.084
Do you have enough bullets?

12:30.121 --> 12:31.353
[ENGINE REVVING]

12:31.389 --> 12:32.555
JEFF: I think I get it.

12:32.590 --> 12:36.992
Your coma sent you to the Realm,
but only your consciousness.

12:37.028 --> 12:39.295
It's like lucid dreaming except...

12:39.330 --> 12:40.396
you're not dreaming.

12:40.431 --> 12:41.464
See, now you're getting it.

12:43.267 --> 12:45.034
But what if you've got this all wrong?

12:45.069 --> 12:46.335
What if none of this is even real?

12:46.370 --> 12:49.238
No, the Realm is definitely real.

12:49.273 --> 12:51.207
Sometimes it feels more
real than being awake.

12:51.242 --> 12:52.341
See, that's what I'm saying.

12:52.376 --> 12:54.477
What if the Realm is the real world,

12:54.512 --> 12:56.445
and this place is just

12:56.481 --> 12:59.148
a simulation that exists in our minds?

12:59.183 --> 13:00.282
What if right now,

13:00.318 --> 13:02.952
you and I are unconscious in the Realm,

13:02.987 --> 13:05.087
and our consciousness is being projected

13:05.122 --> 13:06.989
into this world?

13:07.024 --> 13:08.123
Maybe I'm not even real at all.

13:09.293 --> 13:11.327
[TIRES SQUEALING]

13:14.065 --> 13:15.331
JEFF: I'm gonna take
a wild guess and say that

13:15.366 --> 13:17.199
this is somehow related to our freezer.

13:18.302 --> 13:19.268
[GLASS SHATTERING]

13:20.338 --> 13:23.038
- [GRUNTING]
- Turn around! Turn around!

13:23.074 --> 13:24.440
[TIRES SQUEALING]

13:39.490 --> 13:43.786
Any chance that wasn't real?

13:43.786 --> 13:45.930
Cover as much of the walls as you can.

13:45.930 --> 13:48.664
The aluminum acts as
an electrical insulator.

13:48.699 --> 13:51.066
It will prevent this place from
going up like a Cherries Jubilee.

13:51.102 --> 13:53.102
Have you ever tried Cherries Jubilee?

13:53.137 --> 13:54.870
I'm usually partial to chocolate,

13:54.905 --> 13:56.672
but the sweetness of the ice cream

13:56.707 --> 13:57.806
and the tartness of the...

13:57.842 --> 14:00.976
Edgar, the guy just punched
through my window, man.

14:01.012 --> 14:03.612
Now that psycho could be
on his way over here.

14:03.648 --> 14:04.780
Then I suggest you work fast.

14:10.821 --> 14:13.822
It's a Faraday Cage, isn't it?

14:13.858 --> 14:17.760
And the freezer needs a heavy
dose of electromagnetic energy

14:17.795 --> 14:19.795
for my consciousness to travel, right?

14:19.830 --> 14:21.063
And these walls

14:21.098 --> 14:23.032
will keep the signals outside
from getting in and...

14:23.067 --> 14:24.066
Frying our brains.

14:24.101 --> 14:26.635
[CHUCKLES] You really know your physics.

14:26.671 --> 14:27.903
You didn't tell me you were a scientist.

14:29.040 --> 14:30.973
I'm not.

14:31.008 --> 14:32.975
I wanted to be when I was a kid,

14:33.010 --> 14:35.811
but, uh, life sort of
took a different turn.

14:36.881 --> 14:37.980
Maybe things would be different

14:38.015 --> 14:41.016
if I didn't choose to dig up
freezers and chase visions.

14:41.052 --> 14:43.018
You didn't choose. You were chosen.

14:45.022 --> 14:46.855
Free will is an illusion.

14:46.891 --> 14:48.691
A trick our minds play on us

14:48.726 --> 14:50.959
to make human beings believe we're
in control of our own destinies.

14:52.763 --> 14:54.029
And... we're not?

14:54.065 --> 14:56.031
There's only one correct path,

14:56.067 --> 14:58.701
and it's the one path
you're meant to take.

15:00.805 --> 15:01.970
CHARLIE: So you're okay with this?

15:03.808 --> 15:04.840
Okay with what?

15:04.875 --> 15:06.709
You're putting a lot of trust in a guy

15:06.744 --> 15:09.745
who's had to eat his last
5,000 meals with a spork.

15:09.780 --> 15:11.847
To say nothing of the fact
that he's having us build

15:11.882 --> 15:13.048
a life-size Jiffy Pop.

15:14.085 --> 15:16.652
I trust him as much as I trust you.

15:19.990 --> 15:21.724
[SIGHS]

15:21.759 --> 15:22.991
Okay. I get it.

15:24.128 --> 15:25.894
Last time Holden and I were together,

15:25.930 --> 15:28.030
he got shot and I ran.

15:28.065 --> 15:30.933
I'm not gonna run. Not this time.

15:30.968 --> 15:31.967
[STAPLE GUN CLICKS]

15:32.002 --> 15:33.769
I believe you.

15:33.804 --> 15:34.970
No, you don't.

15:37.675 --> 15:39.041
I believe you because
Holden believes you.

15:47.952 --> 15:49.818
He's lucky to have you
looking out for him.

15:52.156 --> 15:54.656
Ah, it ain't luck.

15:54.692 --> 15:57.793
I'm the reason he knocked his
head and went into that coma.

15:57.828 --> 16:00.662
If it wasn't for me, none
of this would be happening.

16:00.698 --> 16:02.998
If it wasn't for me, maybe
my brother would still be alive.

16:07.705 --> 16:10.639
Look, I know you don't have
a ton of reasons to trust me,

16:10.674 --> 16:11.974
but I also know that the past

16:12.009 --> 16:14.610
will suffocate you if you let it.

16:17.648 --> 16:18.680
Trust me on that.

16:21.819 --> 16:24.987
[DOOR RUMBLING]

16:26.824 --> 16:28.657
It's... gone.

16:31.128 --> 16:32.961
Are you sure we have the right barn?

16:32.997 --> 16:34.830
I'm sure.

16:34.865 --> 16:35.931
They must've moved the machine.

16:38.035 --> 16:39.067
We did.

16:39.103 --> 16:40.869
[GUN CLICKS]

16:40.905 --> 16:42.938
We moved it to a more secure location.

16:42.973 --> 16:44.640
You can see why.

16:44.675 --> 16:46.041
What happened here?

16:46.076 --> 16:47.910
The blood? The gate?

16:47.945 --> 16:49.978
There was an incident.

16:50.014 --> 16:51.847
What kind of incident?

16:51.882 --> 16:54.082
A few of our disciples awoke
from cryogenic hibernation

16:54.151 --> 16:55.984
and brutally murdered six of my men.

16:57.688 --> 16:58.854
That kind of incident.

17:00.057 --> 17:01.056
Where is it?

17:04.060 --> 17:05.594
Why do you want to know?

17:06.696 --> 17:07.796
Someone's coming.

17:07.832 --> 17:09.731
A woman pretending to be FBI.

17:11.035 --> 17:12.733
She knows about your machine.

17:12.770 --> 17:14.703
And you mean to get rid of it
before she gets here.

17:15.973 --> 17:17.873
If you think destroying
that machine will tear down

17:17.907 --> 17:19.942
what we've built, I've
got some bad news.

17:21.078 --> 17:23.744
Faith doesn't collapse so easily.

17:23.781 --> 17:25.714
Frost knew this when he
gave birth to Hollow Sky.

17:25.749 --> 17:27.683
Frost is dead,

17:27.718 --> 17:29.651
and it's time Hollow Sky dies with him.

17:36.093 --> 17:37.793
Frost isn't dead.

17:39.129 --> 17:41.029
He's still very much alive.

17:41.065 --> 17:42.631
[HAMMER CLICKS]

17:43.901 --> 17:44.967
Then take me to him.

17:47.513 --> 17:50.209
How could you not tell me
that Holden was attacked?

17:50.639 --> 17:53.540
And now this guy, he's-he's free?

17:53.576 --> 17:55.375
I mean, what if he goes after Holden?

17:55.411 --> 17:57.344
And what if he hurts him again?

17:57.379 --> 17:58.512
- [PHONE BEEPING]
- What are you doing?

17:58.547 --> 18:00.380
I'm calling Holden. You-You try Luke.

18:00.416 --> 18:02.416
I've already tried. They're not
picking up. Either of them.

18:02.451 --> 18:03.750
- Forget it. I'm not waiting.
- [KEYS JINGLING]

18:03.786 --> 18:05.652
- I'm gonna go look for him.
- No, no, hold on. Diane.

18:05.688 --> 18:07.421
- Stop. Hold on.
- What?

18:08.657 --> 18:10.390
I think I know who can help.

18:10.426 --> 18:12.526
[RUMBLING]

18:16.732 --> 18:17.731
[PHONE BUZZING]

18:20.803 --> 18:22.669
[BUZZING CONTINUES]

18:24.540 --> 18:25.505
What is it?

18:26.642 --> 18:27.741
It's your dad.

18:32.615 --> 18:33.614
This is Jeff.

18:33.649 --> 18:35.749
Jeff. Hey, it's Tom.

18:35.784 --> 18:36.750
Is Holden there?

18:37.786 --> 18:38.785
Yeah, he's right here.

18:38.821 --> 18:40.621
<i>Is everything okay?</i>

18:40.656 --> 18:42.422
TOM: Put him on, will you?

18:46.629 --> 18:47.661
Dad?

18:47.696 --> 18:49.696
<i>Uh, sorry, I must've left
my phone at home.</i>

18:49.732 --> 18:50.731
Are you okay?

18:50.766 --> 18:52.599
- HOLDEN: <i> I'm-I'm fine.</i>
- Where are you?

18:52.635 --> 18:54.368
I'm at Jeff's.

18:55.571 --> 18:56.570
What's going on?

18:56.605 --> 18:58.405
<i>Sheriff Dayton said
that you were attacked,</i>

18:58.440 --> 19:00.507
<i>said that someone went
after you in a parking lot?</i>

19:00.542 --> 19:02.542
Why didn't you say something to us?

19:02.578 --> 19:05.579
I know. I should have, but I
didn't want you to worry.

19:05.614 --> 19:07.547
Well, he got out, the
guy who attacked you.

19:07.583 --> 19:09.549
A gang broke him out
of jail this morning.

19:09.585 --> 19:11.685
<i>They murdered four police officers.</i>

19:11.720 --> 19:13.687
Sheriff Dayton's with us
right now at the house.

19:13.756 --> 19:15.622
We want you to come to the house
so we can keep you safe.

19:15.658 --> 19:16.757
I wanna talk to him.

19:16.792 --> 19:18.558
Holden, honey, please just...

19:18.594 --> 19:20.460
<i>just come home. I need to see you.</i>

19:21.530 --> 19:22.663
HOLDEN: Mom, I...

19:22.698 --> 19:24.498
- [ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]
- Mom?

19:24.533 --> 19:26.566
Holden? Holden?

19:26.602 --> 19:27.701
Hello? Mom?

19:30.472 --> 19:32.339
- What? What happened?
- The line went dead.

19:32.374 --> 19:33.607
- Well, try him again.
- I am.

19:33.642 --> 19:35.008
[LINE RINGING]

19:35.044 --> 19:36.777
VOICEMAIL: <i>Hey, you've reached
Jeff McArdle. I'm not here...</i>

19:36.812 --> 19:38.478
It went straight to voicemail.

19:38.514 --> 19:39.479
[DOORBELL RINGING]

19:43.519 --> 19:44.518
Stay here.

19:49.625 --> 19:51.625
[DOOR OPENS]

19:51.660 --> 19:53.327
TOM: Don't worry. It will be okay.

19:54.763 --> 19:56.463
I...

19:56.498 --> 19:57.731
I knew there was something wrong.

20:00.402 --> 20:01.768
The lying, the bruises...

20:01.804 --> 20:03.370
Hey, hey, hey. Hey.

20:04.406 --> 20:05.572
We did everything we could.

20:05.607 --> 20:07.541
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:07.576 --> 20:08.742
- Hmm.
- [SHERIFF DAYTON CLEARS THROAT]

20:10.579 --> 20:11.611
It was the mailman.

20:11.647 --> 20:12.779
[CHUCKLES]

20:14.783 --> 20:15.782
It's for you.

20:26.528 --> 20:28.362
I can't do this.

20:28.397 --> 20:29.663
Not right now. I...

20:29.698 --> 20:31.531
He's killing people.

20:31.567 --> 20:33.600
He murdered that guy
at the bowling alley

20:33.669 --> 20:35.635
and four others, police, I...

20:35.671 --> 20:37.371
I can't just leave my
family while he's...

20:37.406 --> 20:38.638
If you really want
your family to be safe,

20:38.674 --> 20:40.640
you've got to get into the
Realm and close that portal.

20:41.677 --> 20:42.676
He won't stop.

20:42.711 --> 20:44.711
Every minute you're out
here, his power grows.

20:44.747 --> 20:45.779
I'm sorry, but...

20:46.815 --> 20:48.615
it has to be now.

20:55.591 --> 20:56.757
You're still on board with this?

20:59.528 --> 21:01.628
Someone's gotta make
sure these two lunatics

21:01.663 --> 21:02.696
don't let you drown.

21:09.571 --> 21:10.704
Let's get this over with.

21:13.742 --> 21:15.709
Once your consciousness makes the trip,

21:15.744 --> 21:18.378
you'll be able to communicate
with us through this...

21:18.414 --> 21:19.546
[STATIC ON RADIO]

21:22.451 --> 21:23.550
Where'd you get that?

21:23.585 --> 21:25.786
- Did you...
- That little girl stole my bedroom,

21:25.821 --> 21:28.789
so I'm borrowing her walkie-talkie.

21:29.825 --> 21:32.492
And you sure I'll be able to hear you?

21:32.528 --> 21:35.429
Yes, but not for long.

21:35.464 --> 21:37.464
I'll help you find your way
into the heart of the Realm,

21:37.499 --> 21:38.832
but beyond that...

21:38.867 --> 21:40.400
I'm on my own.

21:41.703 --> 21:44.571
Once you arrive, you gotta
close whatever rift

21:44.606 --> 21:45.806
you opened during your last visit.

21:45.841 --> 21:48.542
You do that and no more
of those Hellspawn

21:48.577 --> 21:49.843
will be able to cross
over into our world.

21:55.517 --> 21:57.818
How... is he supposed to close it?

21:59.621 --> 22:02.322
Yeah. How am I supposed to close it?

22:02.357 --> 22:03.757
The Realm has

22:03.792 --> 22:06.793
a... funny way of communicating.

22:06.829 --> 22:08.595
It will tell you what
it needs from you.

22:08.630 --> 22:11.498
I suggest you give it what it wants.

22:11.533 --> 22:12.766
We'll be right here by your side.

22:34.590 --> 22:35.589
[DOOR CLANKS]

22:38.727 --> 22:40.794
[BUBBLING]

23:07.489 --> 23:10.323
[GASPING]

23:34.816 --> 23:38.485
[WAVES CRASHING]

23:41.723 --> 23:44.624
[GRUNTING, GASPING]

24:05.681 --> 24:09.516
[PANTING]

24:18.760 --> 24:21.494
Oh! Man, I hate this place.

24:30.825 --> 24:32.158
Why are you keeping him alive?

24:32.193 --> 24:33.926
Because I believe he'll wake up.

24:34.996 --> 24:36.095
Others woke up.

24:37.832 --> 24:39.031
He didn't.

24:39.067 --> 24:40.967
Frost is different.

24:41.002 --> 24:43.069
He has a bigger purpose, so he holds on.

24:44.973 --> 24:46.138
You have no idea, do you?

24:48.142 --> 24:49.141
I saw what happened to him.

24:50.211 --> 24:51.177
He's gone.

24:54.015 --> 24:57.884
From what I understand, you and your
father never had much of a bond.

24:57.919 --> 25:01.153
Yeah, 'cause she didn't blindly
worship the jerk like you do.

25:03.157 --> 25:06.826
Your father is, present
tense, a great man.

25:08.897 --> 25:11.063
When he wakes up, he'll show us
all how to reach the Afterlife,

25:11.099 --> 25:12.865
exactly as he foretold.

25:15.837 --> 25:16.936
You wanna talk to him?

25:16.971 --> 25:17.937
[WILLA SCOFFS]

25:26.848 --> 25:28.948
[SIGHS]

25:28.983 --> 25:32.218
I'd like to think regardless of
how my daughter felt about me,

25:32.253 --> 25:34.086
if she saw me in this condition...

25:36.090 --> 25:39.125
she'd at least find it in herself
to pay respect to the effort.

25:54.943 --> 25:56.275
So...

25:56.311 --> 25:57.944
how's your brother?

26:01.182 --> 26:02.882
You weren't a great man.

26:05.219 --> 26:06.919
You were a coward.

26:08.890 --> 26:11.157
I may share your blood,
but I don't inherit your sins.

26:12.994 --> 26:14.794
'Cause I'm stronger than you.

26:16.197 --> 26:17.897
I achieved something you never did.

26:19.200 --> 26:21.801
I realized we're not
meant for that place.

26:21.836 --> 26:24.070
None of us, for any reason.

26:25.139 --> 26:27.206
And I'm going to prove that to anyone

26:27.241 --> 26:29.041
who ever believed in you...

26:34.282 --> 26:35.848
and to anyone who didn't.

26:45.126 --> 26:46.225
What did he say?

26:57.939 --> 26:58.871
PASTOR IAN'S VOICE: <i>Diane...</i>

27:00.108 --> 27:02.074
<i>I'm neither proud of what I've done,</i>

27:03.144 --> 27:05.111
<i>nor who I did it for.</i>

27:06.814 --> 27:09.181
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't do
more to protect your son.</i>

27:11.085 --> 27:14.754
<i>Holden is far more special
than you may know.</i>

27:18.926 --> 27:21.027
<i>You are a wonderful mother.</i>

27:24.866 --> 27:26.032
<i>He's gonna need you.</i>

27:31.839 --> 27:33.939
- [WAVES CRASHING]
- HOLDEN: <i> Okay.</i>

27:35.910 --> 27:36.876
So now what?

27:37.912 --> 27:40.946
Do you see, um, an ocean and a-a light

27:40.982 --> 27:42.248
<i>far off in the distance?</i>

27:50.958 --> 27:53.225
Yeah. Yeah, I see it.

27:53.261 --> 27:55.094
Good. Good. Swim towards it.

27:56.998 --> 27:59.999
Swim... towards it? It's in
the middle of the ocean!

28:00.034 --> 28:01.801
You can make it.

28:01.836 --> 28:04.170
HOLDEN: <i>No. No, I can't make it.
I'll drown!</i>

28:04.205 --> 28:06.105
Not if you swim far enough.

28:06.140 --> 28:08.040
Remember, the Realm
will tell you what if wants.

28:08.076 --> 28:09.842
<i>Just listen to it.</i>

28:19.787 --> 28:20.786
Now...

28:22.090 --> 28:23.155
what does it want?

28:33.000 --> 28:34.200
It wants me to swim.

28:48.950 --> 28:51.817
[WAVES CRASHING]

29:39.267 --> 29:40.933
[GAGGING]

29:40.968 --> 29:43.135
[COUGHING, RETCHING]

30:15.169 --> 30:16.936
What the hell?

30:16.971 --> 30:18.237
This isn't hell...

30:20.274 --> 30:22.041
- nor is this heaven.
- HOLDEN: Frost.

30:24.212 --> 30:26.145
No, no, I-I saw you...

30:26.180 --> 30:28.881
You saw a desperate man standing
in front of the love of his life.

30:30.284 --> 30:32.084
A man given a remarkable gift.

30:33.888 --> 30:35.921
A gift not without a heavy price.

30:36.991 --> 30:39.925
Why the hell should I
believe anything you say?

30:43.097 --> 30:44.263
How do I even know you're real?

30:46.067 --> 30:47.199
Does it matter?

30:50.972 --> 30:51.937
I'm here.

30:54.208 --> 30:55.307
And so are you.

30:57.879 --> 30:59.879
We think of life and
death as a succession,

30:59.914 --> 31:02.248
a sequence of events, but it's...

31:02.283 --> 31:04.817
not that at all.

31:04.852 --> 31:07.953
It's a balance, a cosmic compromise.

31:07.989 --> 31:10.222
You upset that balance

31:10.258 --> 31:12.825
stepping out onto that bridge.

31:15.162 --> 31:17.162
FROST: We upset the balance,

31:17.198 --> 31:20.065
and now you must be prepared
to accept the consequences.

31:21.102 --> 31:22.167
As I have.

31:23.971 --> 31:25.838
That's why you're here, is it not?

31:28.075 --> 31:30.075
Now you have a responsibility
to make things right.

31:31.846 --> 31:34.813
Balance... must be restored.

31:34.849 --> 31:36.181
How do I restore the balance?

31:36.217 --> 31:39.251
You let go of the one thing you've
been holding on to the tightest.

31:41.188 --> 31:43.222
What you're most afraid to give up.

31:44.292 --> 31:45.858
What's that?

31:50.998 --> 31:53.232
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

32:01.142 --> 32:02.808
FROST: You were so young

32:03.844 --> 32:04.977
when your entire life...

32:06.013 --> 32:07.146
changed forever.

32:10.184 --> 32:12.851
You still believe the boy in that bed

32:13.921 --> 32:16.121
has a normal, ordinary
life ahead of him.

32:20.127 --> 32:22.928
You believe he can walk
both paths concurrently.

32:22.964 --> 32:24.863
[MONITOR CONTINUES BEEPING]

32:24.899 --> 32:25.898
I do.

32:27.969 --> 32:29.001
I have to.

32:31.005 --> 32:33.264
Not if you want to save your world.

32:34.208 --> 32:36.041
You can't embrace one path...

32:37.945 --> 32:40.074
while clinging desperately to another.

32:41.849 --> 32:43.215
You want to save all
those people back home?

32:46.220 --> 32:48.053
Then accept what you've
been running from.

32:52.927 --> 32:54.093
What do I have to do?

32:55.229 --> 32:58.063
The Realm requires a
covenant, a blood oath.

32:59.166 --> 33:00.933
The Realm requires a promise

33:00.968 --> 33:02.968
that will forever bind
you to this place.

33:05.072 --> 33:06.839
It requires sacrifice.

33:20.955 --> 33:21.920
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

33:22.957 --> 33:24.156
[CHUCKLES] You...

33:24.191 --> 33:27.159
You want me to what,
stab myself with that thing

33:27.194 --> 33:28.827
while I'm sleeping?

33:29.897 --> 33:31.830
It requires your blood,
so yes, you will...

33:33.167 --> 33:35.901
have to stab yourself with that
thing while you're sleeping.

33:37.838 --> 33:39.171
Try to aim for the heart.

33:42.243 --> 33:43.242
No.

33:44.278 --> 33:46.211
No way. I-I won't do it.

33:48.315 --> 33:50.215
I can't.

33:50.251 --> 33:53.118
It's what the Realm wants.
It's what it needs from you.

33:54.155 --> 33:55.220
Then what?

33:57.158 --> 33:59.825
What happens when I'm
forever bonded to this place?

33:59.860 --> 34:01.827
Your promise will be affirmed.

34:01.862 --> 34:03.862
The hole between worlds will close.

34:03.898 --> 34:05.764
And my world

34:05.800 --> 34:08.132
and the people that I love will be safe?

34:08.168 --> 34:10.034
Balance restored and all that?

34:10.071 --> 34:13.938
Not until the evil you
released has returned.

34:14.975 --> 34:16.809
But first things first.

34:16.844 --> 34:19.244
It's time to put away childish things.

34:27.922 --> 34:28.920
Will it hurt?

34:36.964 --> 34:39.998
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

35:14.235 --> 35:15.234
I'm sorry.

35:19.273 --> 35:20.873
YOUNG HOLDEN: Please...

35:22.843 --> 35:23.876
don't do it,

35:25.813 --> 35:26.845
I-I-I have to.

35:26.881 --> 35:27.946
No, you don't.

35:28.983 --> 35:30.048
I'm not ready.

35:31.952 --> 35:33.952
We're not ready to say goodbye.

35:33.988 --> 35:35.888
There's no other way. I...

35:35.923 --> 35:36.955
Please.

35:38.058 --> 35:39.191
I don't wanna die.

35:39.226 --> 35:40.859
Please, I don't want to die. I don't...

35:41.896 --> 35:43.028
Please. Please...

35:43.063 --> 35:44.897
I'm so sorry.

35:44.932 --> 35:46.265
[GRUNTS]

35:46.300 --> 35:48.267
[MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY]

35:48.302 --> 35:50.969
[ALARM BLARING]

36:02.016 --> 36:04.183
[MONITOR FLATLINES]

36:14.995 --> 36:16.862
[THUDDING, RATTLING]

36:20.901 --> 36:22.201
[HOLDEN GASPING]

36:30.878 --> 36:31.944
I did it.

36:33.047 --> 36:34.046
You did it.

36:35.149 --> 36:36.114
I did it.

36:37.151 --> 36:38.992
Just like he said you would.

36:39.887 --> 36:42.270
- So that's it? We're done?
- HOLDEN: We're not done.

36:42.890 --> 36:43.956
Not yet.

36:45.259 --> 36:49.171
The hole is closed, but that
thing that attacked me...

36:49.171 --> 36:50.611
it's still here.

36:51.298 --> 36:53.265
Balance has to be restored.

36:53.300 --> 36:55.801
So... what does that mean?

36:57.204 --> 36:58.937
It means we have to send him back.

37:04.322 --> 37:05.488
CHARLIE: Holden, wait.

37:05.523 --> 37:07.490
You can't just pack up and head home.

37:07.525 --> 37:08.591
I have to.

37:08.626 --> 37:10.593
He knows I went back in,
and he knows I prevented

37:10.628 --> 37:12.328
more of him from coming through.

37:12.363 --> 37:13.696
He's angry, and he's
looking for a fight.

37:13.732 --> 37:15.298
How do you know he knows?

37:15.333 --> 37:18.267
Because Holden bonded
himself to the Realm.

37:21.406 --> 37:22.638
What the hell does that mean?

37:23.775 --> 37:26.542
It's okay. I'm okay. I...

37:28.379 --> 37:29.345
did what I had to do.

37:30.381 --> 37:31.714
And now we have to get back home

37:31.783 --> 37:34.650
in case that thing comes
for me or my family.

37:34.686 --> 37:35.651
I'm not going with you.

37:37.288 --> 37:39.388
You brought me here to help you
get into the Realm. I did that.

37:40.458 --> 37:42.358
You need to protect your home. I...

37:42.393 --> 37:43.493
I need to get back to mine.

37:45.597 --> 37:47.263
Coldwater? But...

37:48.299 --> 37:49.732
they kept you locked up.

37:49.768 --> 37:51.467
They-They kept me safe.

37:53.404 --> 37:55.271
Safe from others. Safe from myself.

37:57.575 --> 38:00.576
I'm ready to go back and face whatever
the doctors have in store for me.

38:02.714 --> 38:04.313
I belong there.

38:06.417 --> 38:08.518
Listen, I'll take him back to Coldwater.

38:10.288 --> 38:13.256
You get your ass back home and
make sure that everyone's safe.

38:14.592 --> 38:15.625
Sound good to you?

38:22.500 --> 38:24.600
You're always gonna have us, Edgar...

38:24.636 --> 38:26.502
even if we have to break you out again.

38:32.544 --> 38:34.477
Thank you for getting him back safe.

38:35.647 --> 38:36.646
He's not safe.

38:37.715 --> 38:38.714
He'll need your help.

38:40.351 --> 38:42.518
But... you already
knew that, didn't you?

38:47.458 --> 38:49.659
Holden's not the only one
who touched that freezer

38:49.694 --> 38:51.327
and saw something.

38:52.463 --> 38:54.430
The Realm tells you things

38:54.465 --> 38:56.265
and try as I might to ignore them,

38:56.301 --> 38:57.533
the Realm tells me things.

38:59.571 --> 39:01.304
What did it tell you?

39:11.416 --> 39:12.615
Holden's gonna die.

39:18.556 --> 39:20.256
How often are you wrong?

